reviews.review_text:
Great dose of 82 I love this run at the Greek. Between these 3 shows, this night is probably my favourite. Really tight party Dead. Love that Cumberland and the first haf of the second set. All three nights (21-23)are well worth a listen. 
As always, great Charlie Miller sound makes everything seem better!

Weird intro That is the weirdest intro to Man Smart, Woman Smarter that I've heard them play.  Almost sounds at first like they can't remember exactly how it goes until Bob starts in with the lyrics.  Great sound all the way through.
what a Deal!! wow, the most rippin Deal solo I've ever heard hands down!! crazy good... and the Lazy/Sup before is perfect also.  Excellent sound quality, great show!

Dropped four flights The sound on this is fantastic.  I never got to see the band at the Greek, but so many good shows.  Other highlights have been mentioned, but I love the "Tennessee Jed" too.  It's herky-jerky in a really lovely way - Jerry's solo is like a long, clever story that doesn't make you laugh out loud, but is funny and insightful at the same time.

Greek Magic Always loved this whole Greek run, but the Supplication, Deal, China/Rider are so tight! There not the longest versions BUT there so well played & the jams are SO tight that it doesn't matter, just top notch by the whole band! 
Also, the Greek was such a great place to see the GD, like the frost as well. Love me 83-85 Dead but this greek run makes me love 82' as much if not more. The boy's came to play this night. And man did they deliver!
